I am using 3.2 RC4 to attempt to synchronize incoming changes against one of my working sets (lets call it Set1). I select the working set from the java perspective, right click, team->synchronize.

I get a new perspective showing me the incoming changes with 5 projects in that working set are displayed with many changes in each. If the updates do _not_ contain any delete changes (updates and adds seem to work) I can select all 5 projects, choose 'update' from the context menu, and eclipse will go to work and 30 seconds later the view is empty showing no incoming changes.

If any of the projects have atleast one incoming delete the same 'select all 5 then update' process completes within 1-2 seconds with no work done. As long as whatever I highlight does not contain a delete when I select update it works as expected... However I have not been able to get a delete to 1) perform the delete (I have verified selecting a single incoming delete and selecting update does not result in the file being deleted) and 2) The view never removes the incoming delete change since it was never processed.

If more information is needed please contact me and I would be glad to assist. I really would like to see this resolved for 3.2.

None of the files mentioned that are modified have been modified on my file system in months. I don't use external tools and/or the command line cvs client.

No, that's not the trace; that's the console output. If you start Eclipse using the java.exe and provide the debug options file and command line arguments as specified in the link, you would get the trace in the DOS console. Can you tell me the specific version of CVSNT? Also, can you check out our server compatibility page to ensure that the server is supported and is configured properly. Here's the link:

http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/index.cgi/%7Echeckout%7E/platform-vcm-home/docs/online/html-cvs/cvs-compatibility.html

Also, its a long shot, but there is one thing you may want to check. Because CVSNT is case insensitive but Eclipse is case sensitive, you should make sure that the case of the segments of the path you specify for the repository exactly match what the server sends out. I would expect a different error if this were happening but it is possible that you have hit the problem by a different path.

CVSNT version 2.0.51d. I verified it is configured as described in the link you provided. This issue started occuring with 3.2 m6, I did not have synchronize related issues with m5 and below (all other variables constant, this cvs server has not changed configuration or versions in a year or more).

Thanks for all the information. It has been helpful. We changed the way a synchronize was performed late in 3.2. It looks like this has surfaced a bug in CVSNT (i.e. we are sending the proper information to the server but the response from the server is wrong). As a workaround, just disable the preference I mentioned in comment 3 and you should get the same behavior as 3.1.
Glad I could help. Disabling the preference caused it to work as expected, thanks.
Tried this scenario out with CVSNT 2.5.03 and it worked as expected. It looks like CVSNT fixed this issue in their latest release.
